    "MissionGiver": "Citizens for Prosperity",
    "Title": "Stolen Supplies",
    "Description": "Hey,\n\nWe could use your help.\n\nA local we work with was completing a delivery for us, but unfortunately, she ran into some outlaws and had to surrender her ~mission(Item). Silver lining is the outlaws didn\u2019t notice the trackers we placed in the cargo and now we know they\u2019ve taken their haul to ~mission(Location|Address). \n\nWe\u2019d like you to recover the packages for us and finish delivering them to ~mission(Destination|Address). I don\u2019t imagine the outlaws will give them up willingly, but I wouldn\u2019t ask you to put yourself in harm\u2019s way if these supplies weren\u2019t of critical importance.\n\nAlso, to make your life easier, I'd suggest you have a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> with you. \n\nSo, what do you say?\n\nLima Endicott\nLead Dispatcher\nCitizens for Prosperity",
    "DisplayDescription": "Hey,\n\nWe could use your help.\n\nA local we work with was completing a delivery for us, but unfortunately, she ran into some outlaws and had to surrender her [Item]. Silver lining is the outlaws didn\u2019t notice the trackers we placed in the cargo and now we know they\u2019ve taken their haul to [Location|Address]. \n\nWe\u2019d like you to recover the packages for us and finish delivering them to [Destination|Address]. I don\u2019t imagine the outlaws will give them up willingly, but I wouldn\u2019t ask you to put yourself in harm\u2019s way if these supplies weren\u2019t of critical importance.\n\nAlso, to make your life easier, I'd suggest you have a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> with you. \n\nSo, what do you say?\n\nLima Endicott\nLead Dispatcher\nCitizens for Prosperity",
